    "testimony": [
        [
            "NONI MABHALA GCABA",
            "(sworn states)",
            "Unknown"
        ],
        [
            "MS MAYA",
            "Good afternoon Mrs Gcaba.",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "NONI MABHALA GCABA",
            "Good afternoon.",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "MS MAYA",
            "You are going to talk about James Notununu who has passed away.   Is that so?",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "NONI MABHALA GCABA",
            "Yes.",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "MS MAYA",
            "How are you related?",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "NONI MABHALA GCABA",
            "He is my father.",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "MS MAYA",
            "You say that he was detained and tortured.  Do you have any idea how he was tortured?",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "NONI MABHALA GCABA",
            "Yes, he came back and told us that they beat him up on his genitals.  They were tortured in all sorts of ways.",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "MS MAYA",
            "Where was he detained?",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "NONI MABHALA GCABA",
            "Where Mandela was detained.",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "MS MAYA",
            "Was this in Robben Island?",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "NONI MABHALA GCABA",
            "Yes.",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "MS MAYA",
            "Until when was he detained?",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "NONI MABHALA GCABA",
            "It was from 1960 to 1961.  He was very ill.  He was taken to Clarewood and King Edward Hospitals in Durban.  He came back eventually and he passed away at home.",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "MS MAYA",
            "What was he ill of?",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "NONI MABHALA GCABA",
            "He said that he had been given poison to drink.  It affected his lungs.   His one lung collapsed.  The other lung collapsed too and that was when he passed away.\n He came back in 1961.  Then I think he passed away in 1963.",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "MS MAYA",
            "According to your statement he and other detainees were given poison to drink and they all passed away.",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "NONI MABHALA GCABA",
            "Yes, a man from the Mangatywa family, Skunana, they all drank poison and eventually passed away.",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "MS MAYA",
            "Is there anything else that you would like to add?",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "NONI MABHALA GCABA",
            "Well, my mother died.  She had a heart failure and a stroke and passed away.   Because of the whole situation we were left as orphans.",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "MS MAYA",
            "When did your mother die?",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "NONI MABHALA GCABA",
            "In 1985.",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "MS MAYA",
            "Do you have requests.",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "NONI MABHALA GCABA",
            "My parents were buried in separate places Their request before they passed away is that they be buried in the same place.  It means that my father would be exhumed and come and be buried next to my mother.",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "MS MAYA",
            "Where is you father buried?",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "NONI MABHALA GCABA",
            "In Jusana and my mother at my brother's place in Mcobothini.",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "MS MAYA",
            "Thank you madam.  Is that all?",
            "Female"
        ],
        [
            "NONI MABHALA GCABA",
            "Yes thank you.",
            "Female"
        ]
    ]
}